BRUCELLOSIS - MALAYSIA: (NEGERI SEMBILAN) BOVINE, SPREAD
********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 15 Feb 2017 11:36pm
Source: The Sun Daily (Malaysia) [edited]
http://www.thesundaily.my/news/2163528


Negeri Sembilan has been gazetted as a _Brucella abortus_ disease area which can lead to cattle being infected by the disease to suffer miscarriage, sterility and could lead to death [see comment] after 3 cases were detected in the state.

The disease can also infect humans if meat that is infected by the disease is consumed [comment].

Negeri Sembilan Menteri Besar [Chief Minister] Datuk Seri [Malaysian honorary title] Mohamad Hasan said the gazette enabled the Veterinary Services Department to carry out checks on all animal farms to prevent the spread of the disease and facilitating the process of paying compensation to the affected farm operators.

"So far, we have detected 2 or 3 cases in the state where the disease was spread by the imported animals (cattle) which later attacked local cattle. So, in the next 2 or 3 days, we will pass the gazette and the Veterinary Services Department will carry out checks on the animal farms to take blood samples.

"Animals detected to have the disease will be disposed of immediately, and the farmers affected will be given compensation based on the number of animals that had to be disposed of according to the current market price," he said after chairing the EXCO meeting, here today [15 Feb 2017].

Mohamad said the gazette was made according to the Animals Act 1953 and if the gazette was not made, it would pose difficulties to the Veterinary Services Department to carry out its task, while compensation could not be paid out to the farmers affected.

He said members of the public need not panic over the development, as efforts were being taken to prevent the disease from spreading.

